Category: Tocaro Blue Description The Tocaro Blue Gateway serves as a hub to configure and control Tocaro Blue sensor The gateway monitors all connected sensors and transmits their data to secure cloud servers over LTE cellular or WIFI (if available on your boat). In the event of a loss of vessel power, the Gateway has a five day battery When offshore, the gateway stores a record of your voyage to internal memory, and transmits all data to the cloud storage when it A Satellite Transceiver (Optional Feature) ensures location and security data is transmitted anywhere in the All Tocaro Blue sensors operate on the high performance Bluetooth 5 MESH standard this allows longer range wireless communication that is virtually uninterrupted by boat structural Wireless sensors pair to the Gateway with little human interaction, allowing all users to easily install sensor modules and get results in Data is fully encrypted when for complete SPECS: : Bluetooth 5 MESH WIFI: GHz (power saving) CELLULAR: LTE (requires external antenna, included) BATTERY: 5 Days VOYAGE RECORDER: 8 Gb (approximately 6 months) POWER: INGRESS PROTECTION: IP65 OPTIONS: SATELLITE: Iridium (requires external antenna) GPS GLONASS: positioning and navigation (requires external antenna, included) Related products Battery Monitor GPS Module (Coming Soon!) Preventing Unexpected Extubations | ezClinic Home UE Info News About Us Meet Our Team Careers Internships Our Interns Our Interns Contact Us Preventing Unplanned Extubations (UEs) ezClinic empowers ICU nurses to prevent unplanned extubations that pose a risk to million intubated patients annually in the , causing increased trauma, death, escalated provider workflows, and a $5 billion burden in healthcare Patient Action Detection Engine (PADE)™ PADE is a unified AI monitoring and alert system for intubated patients in the ICU that notifies the providers before incidences of unplanned extubations actually occur (the unintentional and uncontrolled removal of the endotracheal breathing tube). More about Merlin "A Sorcerer s Start" Pioneering Legal Technology The Merlin team got its start at a large national law firm where John Tredennick, our founder and CEO, was a longtime trial lawyer, technologist and law In , the firm asked him to become Chief Technology Officer, the first at any major law One of his first steps was to hire a sophisticated team of software developers to build workflow systems that connected the firm’s ten offices across the Litigation Systems: In , the team started offering workflow systems to help legal departments and law firms across the country collaborate in complex, One major engagement involved developing a litigation platform for the defense of qui tam claims against the oil and gas The matter continued for more than a decade, with about clients and law firms coordinating digitally on the The team supported other cases, including a large offshore wage and hours claim against about a dozen major Review Workflow: The team soon began building systems to automate other types of legal review One helped Sears manage advertising review with legal Another, helped Albertson’s manage labor Later, they built a system that helped Wyndham, one of the largest timeshare companies in the world, manage timeshare marketing And several, that are still running today, helped AIG support its reinsurers and manage claims administration across the Awards: These efforts led Microsoft and Adobe to film videos about the team’s projects, cementing their burgeoning reputation as legal After the team won several technology awards that went beyond the legal realm, Adobe’s CEO in nominated them to be enshrined in the Smithsonian Institute as part of the Innovation The firm joined such technology luminaries as Netscape, eBay and Fannie Mae (first mortgage). Catalyst By , so many people were hiring Tredennick’s team for legal technology services the firm decided it was time to spin out the Originally called CaseShare, the company changed its name to Catalyst in , when Tredennick bought the business from his law Over the next decade and a half, the company grew from a handful to more than employees spread across the Data under management grew from a few hundred gigabytes to petabytes stored in five data centers in the and Its clients included many of the largest companies and law firms in the In January , Catalyst was purchased by OpenText, a dollar global technology Not ready to retire, Tredennick founded Merlin Digital Magic, where he is joined by an increasing number of his old team Their goal is to build software using the latest in open source and cloud technology to help clients automate review workflow and streamline compliance Computerworld Smithsonian Innovation Medal Computerworld Smithsonian Award Letter Tredennick Named iris Dating Manifesto — iris Home iris Manifesto EQ Magazine download Home iris Manifesto EQ Magazine download iris Manifesto The online dating industry turned in : a quarter century ago – when the kicked off the era of meeting singles over the internet – fewer than 2% of couples met online (and possibly close to % of them denied it). The proliferation of dating apps and normalization of digital technology as a way to meet has since transformed dating and relationships About half of new US couples now originate While the adoption of online dating is widespread, the industry has not yet solved many of its discontents: some of the complications of dating offline have been shifted (even aggravated) online, and many new issues have come into The list of consumer grievances ranges from to catfishing, from safety concerns to the general inefficacy of many dating iris Project is the informal name of a group of um, engineers – let s just say engineers and digital experts – who have come together to solve consumer problems with the application of Artificial Online dating immediately struck the team as an ideal first industry to focus While there has been no lack of new digital dating communities over the past decade, not many companies have addressed matchmaking technology Replacing tapping with swiping, making the pool look and feel exclusive, or asking women to make the first move don t exactly qualify as technological leaps: those initiatives all have merit, but they are more marketing hooks than matchmaking Dating is the iris Project’s first We believe we can meaningfully improve the experience of digital daters through the personalization of the discovery and messaging stages of online Many of the complaints we ve heard from digital daters have a common denominator: Users complain about how much time is spent scouting these singles marketplaces crowded with people misrepresenting themselves or their intentions, and with members that they simply do not find Many also find the messaging experience stressful and The team at iris is working to solve these issues, and this below is our Authenticity is a must, not an option Deception is the source of many wastes of time: misleading or completely hoax profile pictures, lies about age, height, relationship status are all a dime a dozen on dating And while we can t build an infallible online lie detector (yet), there are plenty of things we can do to keep the lies in We have set off to create a community founded on authenticity, trust and safety: all iris members have to verify the genuineness of their profile This feature is not exclusive to iris, but most dating apps do not require photo verification, they only offer it, meaning that their communities are still crawling with fake profiles , catfish and romance Photo verification is mandatory on iris: approximately % of applications to join are rejected because of profile photo That is only the We have a long roadmap of initiatives to further limit deception in our community: we don t actually believe we will ever develop a robust enough technology to fix humanity and eliminate lies, but we will definitely keep trying to carve out as safe a space as possible for our Dates are more important than dopamine Gamification has been the biggest trend of digital dating in the Tens: following the lead of major social networks, dating apps focused on keeping users engaged as long as The paradigm has been established that the more you swipe , the greater the Those rewards come in the form of dopamine shots released by our own brains every time someone likes us on a dating We’re building an app centered around a less ephemeral outcome: actual iris s core technology was designed to reduce the average amount of time it takes users to form a promising connection We hope to make the Twenties a decade of quality: the better you scan , the faster the Here is how it When users join iris, they begin their experience by scanning profiles randomly presented to them: to scan means to like or pass the pictures of other members – just like on any other dating During this process, iris s Artificial Intelligence analyzes their choices and starts to understand what type of looks they each find attractive (we call each user s type their AttractionDNA®). When our AI begins to get what a user is looking for, it unlocks iris s recommendations: it will then match members based on the statistical likelihood of them liking each The rationale between this matchmaking method is plain: by connecting members that have a greater than average probability of liking each other, we are reducing the number of times users have to swipe left , thus saving people Online dating should not be a game of grading others, it has to be a simple way to connect with we will Transform the Messaging Experience Online dating communities have one, and frustrating thing in common with high schools: popularity is a big And – just like in high school – physical attractiveness play

Overview | Geminos Software by Stu Frost Home Overview Product Services Team News Geminos Industry Stu Frost Blog Contact Select Page Digital Twins for Industry The human race is rapidly moving into a new era of digitization of everything around us, which involves taking data from the physical world and using artificial intelligence (AI) to make better An example of this is cars, but the basic concept is spreading to all different aspects of human behavior, to the point where we’re on the cusp of a new industrial revolution and, ultimately, a huge shift in the way we and the machines we rely on The latest Industrial Revolution, enabled by digitization, is clearly underway and accelerating: Market analysts such as Bain and Growth Enabler estimate that the Industrial Internet of Things (IIoT) market will grow at close to % per annum and reach $80bn-85bn by Chevron estimates that digitization will lead to savings of $3bn by Accenture estimates that the IIoT could add $14.2tn to the global economy by In a recent article in PC Magazine, IDC was quoted as estimating spending on digital transformation would be close to $2 trillion by and also that million new applications are going to be required to facilitate this transformation in the next five At current levels of data scientist and developer productivity, this would require most of the population of China to Right now, this revolution is at risk of stalling a little, because it’s dependent on data scientists to create all of the necessary applications, and there simply aren’t enough of them to meet the enormous level of Geminos makes it much easier to create a ‘digital twin’ of things in the real world, and then build applications that can all talk to one another due to their consistent The facilitated communication between those applications allows for a much higher level of optimization across entire ecosystems (e.g. Smart Manufacturing production lines, Smart Cities, ). Using this approach, the productivity of data scientists and other developers is greatly improved, enabling them to create the next generation of “Using the Geminos approach and platform means that we Amazon Forecast DeepAR+ is a supervised learning algorithm for forecasting scalar (one-dimensional) time series using recurrent neural networks (RNNs). Classical forecasting methods, such as autoregressive integrated moving average (ARIMA) or exponential smoothing (ETS), fit a single model to each individual time series, and then use that model to extrapolate the time series into the In many applications, however, you have many similar time series across a set of These groupings demand different products, server loads, and requests for web In this case, it can be beneficial to train a single model jointly over all of the time DeepAR+ takes this When your dataset contains hundreds of feature time series, the DeepAR+ algorithm outperforms the standard ARIMA and ETS You can also use the trained model for generating forecasts for new time series that are similar to the ones it has been trained Exponential Smoothing (ETS) is a local statistical algorithm for The Amazon Forecast ETS algorithm calls the ets function in the Package forecast of the Comprehensive R Archive Network (CRAN). application of the module is the perimeter protection of any length, designed to prevent intrusion into the protected area from the outside or escape from the It is used to detect people, vehicles, and objects left in the surveillance It is used to protect the perimeter of special facilities (borders, warehouses, prisons), in industrial and manufacturing plants, oil terminals, gas stations, health facilities, schools, and The module is a tool for controlling the loitering on the site, attempts of vehicle lifting on parking lots, the installation of an explosive device on the railway track, unauthorized photo or video shooting, wall Detecting abandoned items (orphaned or forgotten things) allows the user to protect the surveillance area against the appearance of potentially threatening items, for example, of an explosive device, of the owner of the abandoned object on the public, trade and transport infrastructure: railway and bus stations, airports, underground, shopping 3 Face recognition The module captures all the faces in the field of view, matches them against the database and submits the similarity rate for the matched Facial recognition module can be used for: surveillance purposes in crowded places like an airport, a railway station, a subway, a sports complex, a restaurant, a casino, a shopping center, a cinema, a hotel and so access control purposes on secure facilities, passport control points, border control, in agencies, ministries, medical centers, industrial companies, universities, libraries, schools, banks and so 4 Number plate recognition The module for recognition of state registration vehicle number plates provides with control, registration and identification of vehicles at any sites with the traffic of various intensity: parking lots, industrial enterprises, critical objects, road patrol service and municipal authorities, city transport flow control, search for stolen cars, The module is able to recognize number plates issued in more than countries all over the 5 Smoke detection The early smoke detection module is designed to detect smoke by an image from a video camera, allowing the user to determine the source of the fire at a considerable distance from the camera much faster and more accurately, while conventional fire detectors work only when a fire or smoke is in close proximity to The early smoke detection module is used to automatically detect smoke and fires: in residential, administrative and industrial buildings, electrical switchboards in the defense industry, automatic fire suppression systems (for additional visual confirmation of the alarm) in systems of fire detection on the closed platforms, oil terminals, airplanes hangars at sites where the use of standard fire detectors is difficult or 6 Traffic jam and parking The traffic jams detection module is designed to analyze traffic conditions, traffic congestion, monitor traffic flows, and identify traffic jams as well as to control parking zones and count the number of vacant parking The module is used in parking lots, private compounds, highways as well as city roads when special public events might take 7 Vehicles and traffic conditions Traffic violation detection and number plates recognition module is used to detect various types of violations in as well as for calculating the average vehicle speed on the road with a speed The PDDTrack module helps to detect violations where there are no traffic police officers and speed up the analysis of the situation during a traffic The module is used on highways, at the crossroads and dedicated lanes of 8 Crowd detection The Crowd detection module is used for indoor and outdoor perimeter protection for the early warning of public order The module helps to timely detect and prevent dangerous moments: mass riots, crowding, pandemonium, Crowd detection is ideal for monitoring public spaces, event venues, streets, parks, squares, railway stations, underground passages, shopping malls, educational institutions, and capacity restricted 9 Sound detection The audio detector is capable of detecting and recognizing various sounds, such as gunshots, public places significantly reducing the response time of security personne

(part 1) BEING A KID with a birthday in a land where they have Christmas can be a People forget all about it amid the bustle and Or else they get you one ("extra special") gift for both And don t expect great attendance at a children s birthday party held during holiday It s a drag being a December This I can tell So I could’t help feeling a little upwelling of empathy for another "December kid" whose birthday I recently found out: the Net Promoter Score , which celebrated (or mostly didn t) its Sweet last month, having been "born" in a article in the December, HBR: "The One Number You Need To Grow" (Frederick Reichheld, Bain & Harvard Business Review , ). The article is free and worth (re-)reading, as ancient foundational texts often are, especially around times of transition and reflection like the new year (good , ). Then, since sixteen is, well, kind of a milestone age in American culture, kind of a coming of age year, I thought it would be fun to ask, how is turning out? What s it like, as a managment theory entering in ? Is its future looking good? Or should we worry about its grades, or some of the friends it s been making lately? Even if sixteen is still too young for Americans to vote, bank, buy liquor, buy tobacco, or enlist, it is not too young to drive (and feel like you enlisted, if you make your first car a ) Although, I did read recently that the rite of passage known in as "Their First Car" is, according to the the WSJ, yet another thing the kids these days are just "so over" (subs. only) . I guess, for the urban dwelling teenager, what s not to prefer about or ? OK, but even if driving at is on the ebb, there s always college admissions as a rite of passage (or at financial security . OR hotbed of bribery and corruption ). In any race to the top based on a famously standardized ranking mechanism, you know be killin it: ! Or, well, never mind: first the kids aren t driving, and now WaPo tells us they aren t even testing, either !? So truly, nothing is Sorry , looks like this year might be kind of on the slow but speaking of gee, you might be in , but in idea years , why you re solidly "Silver" ! Big Ideas like come and go at quite a clip in an advanced Knowledge Economy like ours (...explained Peabody to "Why, they re almost as fast as dog years!") Speaking of silver, maybe a better analogy for in is the silverback gorilla (or insert your favorite alpha ). Here now is Sir David Attenborough (at , making the rest of us look old): "Targeted by an endless series of younger rivals, and facing inevitable dethronemenet, humiliation and obscurity, the Net Promoter Score bides its Yet, with the eventual fate of its silver head a foregone conclusion, the only questions are When — as in, when will its reign finally end — and Who — as in, who s next?" No one s counting it out yet, but as a mental exercise, what would be next after ? I m never one to turn down just a smidge of wild speculation - but maybe not right here and now, not on Day (Observed). I m tiring of ‘virtual’ and ‘IRL’). Clever content now will give us a leg up when hybrid events start Avoid another hay Better to engage people by challenging them and nurturing connections with a shared Comedy and escape rooms are useful and But the real opportunity is attaching them to meaningful content before, during, and after: People will walk away with a deeper understanding of AI concepts ~ and a smile on their For instance: What should decision makers do when an AI goes off the rails? discovery process begins and ends with our cutting edge computational platform and proprietary molecular This means everything from the strategic identification of viable biological targets to the design of clinical candidates is triaged using the computational This along with our combined decades’ worth of drug discovery expertise (resulting in several clinical candidates and another currently moving through clinical trials) gives us our edge in drug biological pathways & target selection From the very start, our biologists and computational chemists work closely together to make sure that biological pathways and targets are viable for In this way, targets that are unlikely to be druggable are avoided and those with the highest chance of success become the immediate identifying hits Traditional drug discovery often starts with a screen (HTS) of an compound collection containing some millions of The overall process takes several months to complete and usually results in very low hit rates and poor quality Our strategy involves screening a virtual compound collection of billions of No molecule gets synthesized or tested in an assay until it goes through the computational In this way, quicker turnaround times, lower costs, and hit rates that are orders of magnitude higher than traditional HTS are Further, the resulting hits provide higher quality chemical matter starting From Hits to Leads A key aspect of our platform involves a sophisticated design strategy, which strategically transforms a given hit into a strong lead compound with novel patent position (IP) and initial drug Once again, this is realizable on the same large scale with quick turnaround times as during the hit optimization towards Clinical candidacy When optimizing a lead molecule, rather than focusing on a single property at a time, the multiple properties that are needed to move it towards drug candidacy are simultaneously This is done using molecular modeling and AI calculations along with experimental And as more data is generated, the calculations are iteratively refined and the models This “iterative multiparameter optimization” scheme is a very unique aspect of our drug discovery Overall Efficiency While traditional drug discovery tends to spend 5–7 years in the stage with the synthesis of –10000 compounds, we anticipate being able to lower the timeline to 2–3 years with only a few hundred compounds synthesized in Moreover, compounds moving into clinical trials are expected to endure a much lower failure rate (currently % of compounds moving into clinical trials fail). company that specializes in assessing road Leading machine learning researchers developed an pipeline that begins with collecting high definition roadway video and using the machine learning models we develop to automatically identify all roadway distresses according to the full ASTM D6433 The data we collect can be directly imported into Streetsaver PAVER and is highly interpretable and disorders, mood disorders, disorders, along with a personality Integration is the foundation of Healthynox’s While our treatment methods include reviews of assessments, we are interested in the ways in which assessments highlight symptoms, affect and express themselves through your behavior, thoughts, emotions or feelings, and belief It is our belief that the understanding and integration of these aspects can be identified, tolerated and integrated into a life free from distressing symptoms and To this end, Healthynox implements a combination of treatment strategies and methods, such as Internet Cognitive Behavioural Therapy (iCBT), Dialectical Behavioral Therapy (DBT) and Mindfulness Based Stress Reduction (MBSR) Cognitive Behavioral Therapy Cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT) consists of two components: Cognitive Strategies: The therapist and patient work together to identify how certain distorted patterns of thinking are related to the patient’s The therapist then attempts to help the patient evaluate and modify his or her inaccurate or unhelpful thoughts and Behavioral Interventions: Behavioral interventions are derived from learning theory and are used to alter a person’s maladaptive Behavioral interventions help to lessen the associations between an individual’s concerns and his or her maladaptive responses to Behavioral techniques include: Exposure: Patients learn to confront situations they usually avoid, such as a public bathroom for a patient who fears being contaminated or a dog for a patient who is afraid of This is generally a gradual process, moving from less situations to more challenging ones at a rate at which the patient feels Ritual Prevention: Patients learn to manage and decrease ritualistic behaviors, such as compulsive or constantly comparing oneself to The overall goal of the ritual prevention exercise is to reduce anxiety or discomfort caused by certain scenarios or Assertiveness Training: Patients learn to use various strategies for recognizing and acting upon their wants, needs and views while still being respectful and appropriate toward Assertiveness training typically involves in which participants practice clearer and more direct forms of communicating with Improving communication skills can often improve one’s relationships, career opportunities and basic interpersonal Activity Scheduling Behavioral Activation: Patients learn to constructively build routines by incorporating enjoyable events and activities into their weekly An increase in activity and success can have a positive impact on behavior and : Patients learn to identify, analyze, solve problems, and evaluate the effectiveness of their If the results are not satisfactory, patients learn how to troubleshoot to create a better Motivational Strategies : Patients increase their commitment to CBT by learning strategies that can change and boost What to Expect in CBT Treatment CBT is very structured and and requires a joint effort between the therapist and The development of this collaborative relationship is This means that both the patient and therapist must take an active role

We ve created a tutorial video to help you learn to create a design through our website, which you can view You can also learn more on our How It Works Can I talk to someone? You can contact us several different ways to get your questions The easiest and quickest way to get help is to chat with us being clicking that little blue button in the bottom right corner of our Our email is actually directly connected to our online chat, so if you don t need help right away or can t wait around just send us a message at It s always important to be able to talk to some one when you re really stuck and you can always call us at +44 0 during our support How do I download a design? It s free to make as many designs as you like, but in order to download your new design, you will first have to purchase one of our To download a logo follow these instructions: Go to your Saved Designs and click the design you would like to buy Click the Buy button in the top right corner Select your package After your purchase has been processed, you ll be able to download your assets right away from our site on the post purchase Just click Download under the Design Assets section Can I make changes to a design after I purchase? Unfortunately, you cannot change a design after However, before payment you can play with your designs as many times as you want, until you are Design Can I upload my own image to use in my design? Yes, you can add your own foreground and or Play with our style transfer to improve Can I use my own custom font? Unfortunately, you cannot add your own font to a design at this Our algorithm only knows how to work with our current database of thousands of You can choose them in our graphics How do I save my designs? You can save your design at any time by clicking the Save button during You can also undo changes in the editor by clicking the Return On the Saved Designs page, you can copy your project to change it and save a new Can Deflamel help me design? We can definitely help you design and customize your project, but we still highly recommend you spend some time playing with your You can learn to create your own design on our website by viewing our video: If you require design assistance after using the AI generator and editor, you can purchase the Senior Designer Time This includes one hour of time with our designer who will complete the work on your Payment Do I need to make a payment? You can use Deflamel and save as many designs as you want for However, if you want to download and absorb the copyright, you’ll need to purchase the How much does design cost? We have three packages in varying price ranges to suit your needs, click here to find out Can I get a discount? Please, follow our special offers and What payment methods do you accept? We accept credit cards, as well as After accepting the purchase by using Visa or MasterCard, a secure window with the CloudPayments processing service will open, where you need to enter the information of your Secure is used for additional user If your bank supports this technology, you will be redirected to their server for additional You can find more information about additional authentication methods by contacting the bank, which issued the card to Can I get a refund? As per our Terms of Service , we do not issue refunds following the download of files because there s no guarantee that these files will not be used following the Copyright Do I own the full copyright to my purchased design? You re free to use your purchased design for any commercial or use, and have full ownership of The copyright however, applies to your design as a whole and not the individual If you need evidence in a copyright case, you can use your purchase dates on your receipt as proof of Will other people be able to use my design once I buy it? Because you ve made your own design, it will be personalized to you and the chances of someone creating an identical design are You use different design elements from our database of millions of unique images and fonts, combining their number and location and applying different However, there is always a chance that someone else in the world will create a similar design, but such a chance tends to It s important to know that no person, agency, or designer can guarantee that no one will ever come up with a similar Design Wizard Book Cover Design API How It Works Pricing FAQ Blog Grand Street Unit #137 New York, NY +1 Facebook Instagram Pinterest Linkedin Privacy Policy Terms & Conditions © Copyright, All Rights Reserved by Deflamel We use cookies to give you a better By c

That is Let the machines do it for $5 month per Thats practically Contact us to get Enagements Professional Services If you are looking for automation for your ad campaigns and don t know where to start we can guide you through the process of obtaining Google Ads and Facebook business APIs and automate your © Castle Rock AI | Cordmar Drive, Castle Rock, WA   SKAG Strategies | Castle Rock AI Products Support Blog SKAG Strategies 05 01 Automation Digital Marketing Automation AI SKAG Put a real SKAG strategy into place A SKAG is a “single keyword ad group”. A SKAG is a method Google Ad gurus use to optimize Google The idea is that it saves you money and gets you more relevant targets for the ads you are serving There are some great writeups on the KlientBoost has written the best one that I’ve But there are also those that think SKAGs are One of the core features of the Aderator is the ability to automatically generate There is some forms to fill out, but its less work than any other method to create Plus, we add the benefit of suggesting a bid Our strategy is simple: You pay less to Google to get more The Strategy The Aderator SKAG strategy works as follows: Select a Campaign Select the Keywords you think relevant Create a template for the ad shown Generate the SKAGs Monitor Performance Let’s explain each of these steps to make it more clear: Step 1: Select a Campaign Let’s assume you have a campaign That campaign will already have phrase match, exact match, and broad matches within Broad Match - When some subset of our keywords are in the users search, our ad will show Phrase Match - The keywords should be in the same order how the user typed them, plus some more So if we want to serve ads when the user types in “Big Blue Bus” then if they type “Big Honkin’ Fat Blue suede shoes Bus” then our ad will also Exact Match - Only if the user types in exactly what we Nothing more, nothing Obviously Broad matches will get your ad shown Then Phrase match, and Exact Match will be shown the When we query all the search terms that set off our ads, then we can see which ones got clicks, which ones got conversions, and how many impressions each ad Our SKAGS will now be built from this list of keywords! Step 2: Select the keywords that are relevant From this list you will see all the strange things people type, including misspellings, exotic searches and other It can be somewhat entertaining to go through this You can select two things here: Terms you want to make SKAGs from Terms you want to negate You may find there are keywords that keep showing up that have nothing to do with your Shut those off so you don’t spend money on this junk! But the other words can be gold! Suppose you are selling disco If your ads keep showing up for the game “Disco Elysium” you probably want to negate that keyword on a broad However, if you find someone was searching: “where can I spend a lot of money on a disco ball” and you got 4 conversions out of it, then for goodness sakes, let’s SKAG that keyword! Step 3: Create a Template for the Ads The most effective SKAGs have the keyword in the Ad We can make most of our ads the same, but have one part of the headline change to For example, suppose I’m running an ad for high end My company is called I can make an Ad template that looks as follows: SuperDuperAdventures | < keyword | Luxury High Adventure Then I can fill in that <keyword with each Ad I This gives me a bulk way of loading Obviously, we may need to refine a bit on some of For the “where can I spend a lot of money on disco balls” we might instead change that to be “Luxury Disco Balls”. Step 4: Generate the SKAGs At this point you’ll have to select which Campaign you want to put all of these SKAGs In the past, we normally select the initial farming campaign and append it with SKAG, or some other This part is all very time consuming if you do it The point is, this is a simple exercise you can go through once a week looking at previous words that were generated from search Each week your campaign becomes more With our SKAGs, we only put exact matches in, give the campaign a reasonable budget and over time take budget from the original farming campaign and move into the SKAG This is impossible to do However, using the Aderator can do this for you and allows you to spend 5 minutes a week Step 5: Monitor performance There are two points to evaluate performance: ROAS How much revenue did you get for every dollar spent on advertizing? ISSN (Online) ISSN (Print) ​ The AIRES Network promotes ethical AI awareness through hosting discussions and conferences with chapters of the AI Robotics Ethics Society and other affiliated AIRES Facilitators within AIRES Outreach programs educate local communities at the high school and collegiate levels on the latest breakthroughs and achievements in the field of AI and Robotics ​ AIRES Beyond the Turing Test podcast discusses the ethics of artificial intelligence and educates the audience on societal issues that stem from the impact that artificial intelligence (AI) has or will have on AIRES Constitution (under revision) ©2020 by the AI Robotics Ethics Society   AIRES Faculty Committee | AI Robotics Ethics Society AI Robotics Ethics Society ® Initiative Home About AI Ethics Journal METRA Program Chapters AIRES Faculty Committee Podcast Start an AIRES Chapter Contact More AIRES Faculty Committee ​ Yutao He Edward Parson Alex Alben, UCLA Law Alex Alben is a law professor, technology executive and privacy expert, who served as Washington State’s first Chief Privacy Officer from to In that capacity, he worked on consumer privacy legislation and coordinated privacy and data policy for state and local As one of only five Chief Privacy Officers in the country, Alex initiated statewide programs for enhanced privacy training, consumer education and legal In March of , Gov Tech Magazine named him one of the country’s top “Doers, Dreamers and Drivers” in state As a technology executive for over years in the Seattle area, Alex worked for founded by Paul Allen and Bill He currently serves as faculty at the UCLA School of Law, teaching “Privacy, Data and ” Phebe Vayanos USC Center for Artificial Intelligence in Society Phebe Vayanos is an Assistant Professor of Industrial & Systems Engineering and Computer Science at the University of Southern California, and Associate Director of the CAIS Center for Artificial Intelligence in Prior to joining USC, she was a lecturer

The Current State of AI in Human Resources On the surface, it seems a little ironic that computers would be taking over elements of a job that’s all about human interactions, but when you dig a little deeper, it actually makes a lot of In fact, relying on AI for data management and analysis enables HR personnel to spend more time interacting with people, meaning that technology is helping bring people together, not tear them Let’s see how it Addressing Employee Questions There are certain times of year that everyone is clamoring for time with their favorite HR generalist (i.e., Performance Reviews, Annual enrollments). And for many HR generalists, the same questions are asked over and over again, though perhaps phrased a bit Well, enter the Virtual Assistant (or Chatbot or Virtual Agent)! No matter what you call it, Virtual Assistants (VA) have been designed to understand human language using artificial These VA’s can be trained to understand multiple variations of particular questions and offer prescribed answers to help address employee’s needs promptly and In addition, VA’s do not require sleep or rest, so if an employee needs help at 1 am, their VA is ready and willing to Already organizations are deploying VA’s to help employees answer questions concerning health insurance needs, freeing up valuable resources to address higher priority New Age of Recruitment When trying to sift through dozens (or hundreds) of new hire applications, much of that time is Either you’re spending time looking at candidates who don’t fit your needs, or you are taking significant time categorizing those that are This does not include the time necessary to correspond with potential candidates and secure interview What if a computer system could handle all of that for you? He began the Automunge project as a learning and building experiment in and through the development process discovered the potential to solve some unmet needs in the data science Where we hang our hat — Altamonte Springs, FL   AutoMunge Home About Us Schedule Appointment Contact Us Schedule Artificial Learning, Intelligent Machines Open Source Automated Automunge is automating the practice of to prepare structured data sets for the direct application of machine learning algorithms in the framework of a user’s Taking as input an arbitrary “tidy” structured set (one feature per column and one observation per row), the tool fully automates the numerical encoding and normalization of dataframe feature sets such as to allow for training of predictive algorithms as well as subsequent consistent processing to generate predictions from a trained Automunge is not yet a replacement for feature engineering, however is is suitable as a replacement of the final steps of data preparation prior to the application of machine Inquiries and feedback are Our Blog We have been documenting the development of this tool via regular essays published on Our Blog Automunge solves the problem of data set encoding which in mainstream practice often requires a manual Further, the tool automates the prediction of infill values for missing points in a set using machine learning models trained on the rest of a set in a fully generalized and automated — Nicholas Teague Full documentation and download instructions available on GitHub at AutoMunge #to install to python: pip install Automunge Follow us on twitter at !
